summary: A young woman films herself as she attempts to learn and recite numbers 1-10 in French, Russian, German, and Italian. She uses online resources and her own hand gestures to aid her learning process. The video ends with her encouraging viewers to subscribe and thanking them for watching.
on_screen_text: do you guys like my hand motions i was very concentrated
transcript:
Hi guys. I'm very bored and have nothing better to do with my life right now. So, what's more fun than to watch me learn one through ten in five different languages.

My five languages: French, Russian, Japanese, German and Italian.
Let's start with French.
Un, deux, trois, quatre, cinq, six, sept, huit, neuf, dix.
My mommy taught me these. So.

This is Russian btw.
Agun, dva, tri, chetyre, pyat', shest', sem', vosem', devyat', devyat'.
My pronunciation might be off but.
Let's do Japanese.
Ichi, ni, san, shi, go, roku, nana, hachi, kyu, ju.

Let's do German now.
Einz, drei, drei, vier, funf, sechs, sieben, acht, neun, zehn.
That concludes my video. Thanks you guys so much for watching. If you guys did not like my hand motions, I was very concentrated.
Last but not least is Italian. I love Italy so much.
Uno, due, tre, quattro, cinque, sei, sette, otto, nove, dieci.

Bye bye.
